# SIFT Examiner Portal — frontend dev env (example)
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and adjust. These ONLY affect the Vite dev proxy
# (`npm run dev`); they have no effect on the production build/bundle.
#
# The default dev flow uses mock data (open the app with `?mock=1`) and needs
# NO proxy, so neither var is required just to start the dev server.

# Gateway the dev proxy forwards `/portal/api/*` to (HTTPS, private CA).
# Default: https://192.168.122.81:4508
VITE_API_PROXY=https://192.168.122.81:4508

# Path to the VM CA PEM used to VERIFY the gateway's TLS cert (no secure:false).
# If this file is absent the dev server still starts and falls back to an
# UNVERIFIED proxy (dev-only, logs a warning). Prod/live must point this at the
# real CA so TLS is actually verified.
# Default: /home/yk/.sift-vm-ca-192.168.122.81.pem
VITE_PROXY_CA=/home/yk/.sift-vm-ca-192.168.122.81.pem
